## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

This tile provides a service broker for Pivotal Cloud Foundry to connect to Dell
EMC Elastic Cloud Storage (ECS). ECS is an object storage platform providing a
number of object and file storage protcols, including S3, Swift, HDFS, NFS & Atmos
for both private and public cloud deployments.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

ECS Service Broker for PCF includes the following key features:

* Ability Create and Bind Apps to ECS S3 Buckets
* Ability to Create and Bind Apps to private ECS namespaces
* Support for PCF Volume Services via ECS NFS
* Parallel access to data via both S3 & NFS protocols for file-enabled buckets
* Customized Catalog Services and Plans
* A variety of bucket features, including quotas, encryption, retention &
compliance
* Upgrade beteween bucket plans with different quotas and other bucket features
* Support for multi-site buckets
* Per Application Binding ACLs (read-only, read-write, etc.)

